**Q1: WHAT is spark?**

| CONCEPT            | DETAILS                                                                 |
|--------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Definition         | Distributed in-memory computing engine for large-scale data processing  |
| Driver (Master)    | Manages everything, creates partitions                                  |
| Executor (Worker)  | Each partition processes alone on executor                              |
| Partition          | Data split into chunks across servers (default 128MB per partition)     |
| Example            | 100 Zomato servers, 1 crore orders/day (10GB data) → 200 partitions     |

