**Q2: diff between MapReduce / SPARK / PANDAS**

| MAPREDUCE          | SPARK              | PANDAS             |
|--------------------|--------------------|--------------------|
| Disk-based processing | In-memory processing | Single machine only |
| Slower for iterative | 100x faster than MR | Limited to GB-scale |
| Batch only         | Unified engine     | No fault tolerance |

---

**Q3: diff between RDD / DATAFRAME / DATASET**

| RDD                | DATAFRAME          | DATASET            |
|--------------------|--------------------|--------------------|
| No schema          | Has schema         | Has schema         |
| No optimization    | Catalyst optimizer | Catalyst + Tungsten|
| Compile-time safety| Runtime safety     | Compile-time safety|
| All languages      | All languages      | Java/Scala only    |
| Low-level API      | High-level API     | Type-safe API      |

---

**Q4: What is Transformation?**

| TRANSFORMATION     | DETAILS                                                                 |
|--------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Definition         | Instructions to modify data, returns new RDD/DataFrame                  |
| Execution          | Does NOT compute immediately (lazy)                                     |

---

**Q5: What is Narrow Transformation?**

| NARROW TRANSFORMATION | DETAILS                                                             |
|-----------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Definition            | Each partition processed independently on ONE executor             |
| Data Shuffle          | NO data shuffle between partitions                                  |
| Speed                 | FAST                                                                |
| Examples              | map, filter, union                                                  |

---

**Q6: What is WIDE Transformation?**

| WIDE TRANSFORMATION | DETAILS                                                             |
|---------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Definition          | Partitions exchange data ACROSS executors via network              |
| Data Shuffle        | YES, data shuffled between partitions                              |
| Speed               | SLOW due to SHUFFLE                                                 |
| Examples            | groupBy, join, sort, distinct                                      |

---

**Q7: what is Action?**

| ACTION              | DETAILS                                                                 |
|--------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Definition         | Triggers execution of all transformations                              |
| Execution          | Spark waits until Action is called (Lazy Evaluation)                   |
| Examples           | count(), show(), collect(), save()                                     |

---

**Q8: what is lazy evaluation?**

| LAZY EVALUATION     | DETAILS                                                                 |
|--------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Definition         | Transformations are NOT executed immediately                           |
| Execution Trigger  | Executes only when an Action is called                                 |
| Benefits           | Optimizes execution plan, reduces unnecessary computation              |
| How it works       | Builds DAG of transformations → executes at Action time                |

---

**Q9: RDD Definition**

| RDD - Resilient Distributed Dataset | DETAILS                                                             |
|-------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Resilient                           | Can recover from failures (recomputes lost partitions)             |
| Immutable                           | Cannot change once created (new RDD on transformation)             |
| Fault-tolerant                      | Rebuilds lost data using lineage (DAG)                             |
| Partitioned                         | Split into chunks across cluster                                   |
| Definition                          | Immutable, fault-tolerant collection of objects partitioned across cluster |

---

**Q10: SPARK HIERARCHY (How Jobs are Born)**

| LEVEL               | DETAILS                                                                 |
|--------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Job                | Created whenever an Action is called                                   |
| Stage              | Job split into Stages at every Shuffle boundary (Wide Transformation)  |
| Task               | Smallest unit of work, one Task runs on one Partition of data          |

---

**Q11: Why Apache Spark? What problem it solves?**

| PROBLEM                     | SOLUTION BY SPARK                                                    |
|-----------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------|
| MapReduce slow for iterative| 100x faster using in-memory computation                              |
| Multiple engines needed     | Single unified engine (batch, streaming, SQL, ML, Graph)             |
| No query optimization       | Lazy evaluation with DAG optimizer and Catalyst                      |
| Limited language support    | Rich APIs (Java, Scala, Python, R)                                   |
| HDFS replication overhead   | Fault tolerance via lineage (no replication needed)                  |

