Before spark2 both dataframe and dataset are 2 different things..
In spark2 they merged these 2 into a single unified spark dataset API ( structred API)



whenever we are woking with dataframe or dataset we are dealinng with highe level programming constructs.
when we are working with raw rdd that was a low level code.

spark compailer will convert your high level code (dataframe or dataset) to low level rdd code.
driver will convert your high level code in low level rdd code and then it will send the low level code to executors.

when we are dealing with rdd the code directly goes on executor and run.
when we are dealing with dataframe or dataset our high level code run on driver and driver do the rest i.e conversion of high level code to low level and send it to the executor.

