Shuffle Sort Merge Join
This is more preferable over Shuffle Hash Join, considering its consistency over different cases. These joins happen in three stages:

Repartitioning on both tables will happen based on the joining keys using hash partitioning, providing 200 partitions (as per the default shuffle partitions config; default value is 200).
Sorting of data happens on each partition individually.
As a last step, merging happens based on the joining key.

Tips to make this join happen:

It should be an Equi-join.
Hint it as a Merge join for one of the sides.


